ugh it is ultimately akin to the Germanic name <i>Theodoric</i> (  see  <b>Terry</b>   )."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Efa F Gruffydd ap Tudur of Penhwnllys was born about 1279, in Llangoed, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Gruffydd foel ap Gruffydd, was 31 and her mother, Anne verch Robert, was 31. She had at least 2 sons with Gruffydd Ap Heilyn. She died in 1320, in Wales, at the age of 42."},"et":{"Abt 1279–1320":"umbes 1279–1320","1279–1320":"1279–1320","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1265–1340":"1265–1340","1300–1370":"1300–1370","1322–1405":"1322–1405","1250–1289":"1250–1289","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1340":"1340","Abt 1279":"umbes 1279","1250":"1250","1370":"1370","1290":"1290","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1289":"1289","1322":"1322","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","about 1289":"umbes 1289","1405":"1405","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales","Penrhyn by Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Penrhyn by Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Penhwnllys, Llangoed, Anglesey, Wales":"Llangoed, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1279–1320":"noin 1279–1320","1279–1320":"1279–1320","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1265–1340":"1265–1340","1300–1370":"1300–1370","1322–1405":"1322–1405","1250–1289":"1250–1289","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1340":"1340","Abt 1279":"noin 1279","1250":"1250","1370":"1370","1290":"1290","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1289":"1289","1322":"1322","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","about 1289":"noin 1289","1405":"1405","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales","Penrhyn by Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Penrhyn by Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Penhwnllys, Llangoed, Anglesey, Wales":"Llangoed, Anglesey, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1279–1320":"environ 1279–1320